@startuml
title Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) - Conceptual Flow

actor Attacker
participant "Web Application" as Web
database "Database" as DB
participant "Victim Browser" as Browser
actor Victim

Attacker ->> Web: Submit comment containing malicious script
Web ->> DB: Store comment without sanitization

Victim -> Web: Request webpage with comments
Web -> DB: Load stored comments
DB --> Web: Return comments (including script)

Web --> Browser: Send page with embedded script
Browser -> Browser: Execute script in victim's session

Browser ->> Attacker: Send stolen session data

note over Web
Security failure:
User input not sanitized
before storing or rendering
end note

note over Browser
Script runs with the
victim's permissions
in the browser
end note

@enduml